frameDefinitions: An Agent leaves behind a Theme effectively rendering it no longer within their control or of the normal security as one's property.
A Suspect has been investigated and has a warrant issued for his or her arrest on certain Charges. '

A Suspect in a Current_jurisdiction is forced by Authorities (of the Current_jurisdiction) to go to the Crime_jurisdiction, i.e. the jurisdiction which requested that the Suspect be handed over for trial for a crime which he or she is suspected to have committed in the Crime_jurisdiction.
A particular Binding_principle is (or is not) operative, that is, any obligations, restrictions, and any other aspects of the Binding_principle are (or are not) in effect.
A Perceiver determines the Location of a Sought_entity within a Ground.
The Authorities hold a Suspect under suspicion of having committed a crime (Charges).

listRoleDefinitions: The <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex> is the person who acts to leave behind the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fex name='Theme'>Theme</fex> is the entity that is relinguished to no one from the <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex>'s possession.

The <fen>Suspect</fen> is suspected of having committed a crime by the authorities who want the <fen>Suspect</fen> to enter the criminal process.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> act on behalf of the <fen>Current_jurisdiction</fen>, giving up the <fen>Suspect</fen> to the Crime_jurisdiction.
The jurisdiction (generally a nation) the <fen>Suspect</fen> starts off in.
The jurisdiction (generally a nation) to which the <fen>Suspect</fen> is sent.
The Suspect is forced to go to the jurisdiction where a crime he or she is suspected of took place or is being tried.
The time at which  the <fen>Suspect</fen> is moved.
The location where the extradition occurs.
The <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is the law, contract, principle, or other (set of) obligations that is (or is not) operational.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is in effect.
The <fen>Place</fen> at which the <fen>Binding_principle</fen> is or is not operational.

The <fen>Authorities</fen> hold the <fen>Suspect</fen> in custody.

When the detaining occurs.
Where the detaining takes place.
